WEBVTT

1
01:35:30.876 --> 01:35:34.280
What's happened?
What's the mean of all of this?

2
01:35:34.513 --> 01:35:36.382
It's about the future. Madam Chancellor.

3
01:35:37.283 --> 01:35:42.621
Some people think
the future means the end of history.

4
01:35:42.855 --> 01:35:46.492
We haven't run out of history quite yet.

5
01:35:46.726 --> 01:35:50.896
Your father called the future...

6
01:35:51.130 --> 01:35:55.501
..."the undiscovered country".

7
01:35:56.168 --> 01:35:58.504
People can be
very frightened of change.

8
01:36:03.476 --> 01:36:05.644
You've restored my father's faith.

9
01:36:06.846 --> 01:36:09.782
And you've restored my son's.

10
01:36:55.728 --> 01:36:58.397
Once again. we've saved civilization
as we know it.

11
01:36:58.664 --> 01:37:01.000
And they're not going to prosecute.

12
01:37:01.233 --> 01:37:04.537
They could have prosecuted me.
I felt like Val'eris.

13
01:37:04.770 --> 01:37:07.540
They don't arrest people
for having feelings.

14
01:37:07.773 --> 01:37:12.878
And it's a good thing. too. If they did.
we'd all have to turn ourselves in.

15
01:37:13.979 --> 01:37:17.917
- Captain Kirk.
- Captain Sulu.

16
01:37:18.184 --> 01:37:21.821
As much to the crew of the Enterprise.
I owe you my thanks.

17
01:37:22.455 --> 01:37:27.993
Nice to see you in action one more
time. Captain Kirk. Take care.

18
01:37:39.238 --> 01:37:43.943
- My God. that's a big ship.
- Not so big as her captain.

19
01:37:44.176 --> 01:37:47.713
So... This is goodbye?

20
01:37:48.848 --> 01:37:51.617
It's about time
we got underway ourselves.

21
01:37:51.851 --> 01:37:54.920
Captain. I have orders
from Starfleet Command.

22
01:37:55.154 --> 01:38:00.326
We're to put back to space dock
immediately... to be decommissioned.

23
01:38:14.140 --> 01:38:19.412
If I were human.
I believe my response would be:

24
01:38:19.645 --> 01:38:21.480
"Go to hell."

25
01:38:24.850 --> 01:38:26.452
If I were human.

26
01:38:30.489 --> 01:38:31.957
Course heading. Captain?

27
01:38:38.464 --> 01:38:41.000
Second star to the right.

28
01:38:42.134 --> 01:38:44.003
And straight on 'til morning.

29
01:39:00.853 --> 01:39:04.623
Captain's log. stardate 9529. 1.

30
01:39:04.857 --> 01:39:08.794
This is the final cruise of the Starship
Enterprise under my command.

31
01:39:09.061 --> 01:39:10.863
This ship. and her history-

32
01:39:11.097 --> 01:39:13.866
- will shortly become
the care of another crew.

33
01:39:14.100 --> 01:39:17.770
To them and their posterity
will we commit our future.

34
01:39:18.003 --> 01:39:20.306
They'll continue the voyages
we have begun -

35
01:39:20.539 --> 01:39:22.675
- and journey
to all the undiscovered countries -

36
01:39:22.942 --> 01:39:27.713
- boldly going where no man.
where no one...

37
01:39:27.980 --> 01:39:30.583
...has gone before.

38
00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:26.400
Stardate 9521.6.

39
00:03:26.640 --> 00:03:31.360
Captain's log U.S.S. Excelsior.
Hikaru Sulu commanding.

40
00:03:31.600 --> 00:03:36.240
After three years I've concluded my first
assignment as master of this vessel-

41
00:03:36.480 --> 00:03:41.000
- cataloguing gaseous planetary
anomalies in Beta Quadrant.

42
00:03:42.160 --> 00:03:45.040
We're heading home
under full impulse power.

43
00:03:45.280 --> 00:03:47.840
I'm pleased to report that ship and
crew have functioned well.

44
00:03:48.040 --> 00:03:52.160
According to this. we've completed
our survey of the entire sector.

45
00:04:03.560 --> 00:04:06.040
I have an energy wave at
240 degrees mark six port.

46
00:04:06.280 --> 00:04:07.800
Visual!

47
00:04:09.080 --> 00:04:11.320
My... God!

48
00:04:15.200 --> 00:04:16.640
Shields. Shields!

49
00:04:26.680 --> 00:04:28.240
She's not answering her helm.

50
00:04:28.480 --> 00:04:31.160
Starboard thrusters.
Turn her into the wave.

51
00:04:35.200 --> 00:04:37.560
Go to impulse power.

52
00:04:44.000 --> 00:04:47.520
- Damage report.
- Checking all systems.

53
00:04:54.040 --> 00:04:56.800
- That was no meteor shower.
- Negative. sir.

54
00:04:57.040 --> 00:05:01.560
The sub-space shock-wave
originated at bearing 323.75.

55
00:05:01.800 --> 00:05:05.680
Location... It's Praxis. sir.
It's a Klingon moon.

56
00:05:05.920 --> 00:05:09.800
Praxis is their
key energy production facility.

57
00:05:11.800 --> 00:05:16.200
Send to Klingon High Command. "This
is Excelsior. a Federation Starship."

58
00:05:16.440 --> 00:05:19.760
"We have monitored
a large explosion in your sector."

59
00:05:20.000 --> 00:05:23.320
- "Do you require assistance?"
- Aye. sir.

60
00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:28.040
- Mr Vultane. any more data?
- I've confirmed Praxis' location. but...

61
00:05:29.400 --> 00:05:32.800
- I cannot confirm Praxis' existence.
- On screen.

62
00:05:34.440 --> 00:05:37.520
- Magnify.
- Computer enhancement.

63
00:05:39.760 --> 00:05:41.880
- Praxis?
- What's left of it. sir.

64
00:05:42.120 --> 00:05:44.440
Captain. I'm getting a message
from Praxis.

65
00:05:44.680 --> 00:05:46.520
Let's have it.

66
00:05:58.640 --> 00:06:02.160
This is Brigadier Kerla.
speaking for the High Command.

67
00:06:02.400 --> 00:06:05.600
There has been an incident on Praxis.

68
00:06:05.840 --> 00:06:11.320
However. everything is under control.
We have no need for assistance.

69
00:06:11.560 --> 00:06:17.800
Obey treaty stipulations
and remain outside the Neutral Zone.

70
00:06:18.040 --> 00:06:22.200
This transmission ends now.

71
00:06:22.440 --> 00:06:25.120
- An incident?
- Do we report this. sir?

72
00:06:25.360 --> 00:06:26.840
Are you kidding?

73
00:06:34.040 --> 00:06:37.680
- What are we doing here?
- Maybe it's a retirement party.

74
00:06:37.920 --> 00:06:39.600
That suits me. I just bought a boat.

75
00:06:39.840 --> 00:06:43.760
I'm supposed to be chairing
a seminar at the Academy.

76
00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:47.520
- Isn't this just for top brass?
- Where is Sulu?

77
00:06:47.760 --> 00:06:51.960
Captain Sulu?
On assignment. Where's Spock?

78
00:06:59.480 --> 00:07:04.240
This briefing is classified.
Ladies and gentlemen. the C-in-C.

79
00:07:09.920 --> 00:07:12.080
As you were.

80
00:07:14.800 --> 00:07:17.360
I'll break
this information down succinctly.

81
00:07:17.560 --> 00:07:20.960
The Klingon empire
has 50 years of life left.

82
00:07:22.000 --> 00:07:27.400
For full details. I'm turning this briefing
over to Federation Special Envoy.

83
00:07:39.200 --> 00:07:40.880
Good morning.

84
00:07:41.120 --> 00:07:46.880
Two months ago a Federation Starship
monitored an explosion on Praxis.

85
00:07:47.120 --> 00:07:51.600
We believe it was caused by over-mining
and insufficient safety precautions.

86
00:07:51.840 --> 00:07:55.400
The moon's decimation means
deadly pollution of their ozone.

87
00:07:55.640 --> 00:08:00.440
They will have depleted
their oxygen supply in 50 Earth years.

88
00:08:01.760 --> 00:08:03.360
Due to their enormous military budget -

89
00:08:03.600 --> 00:08:08.960
- the Klingon economy doesn't have the
resources to combat this catastrophe.

90
00:08:09.200 --> 00:08:12.680
Last month. at the behest of
the Vulcan Ambassador. -

91
00:08:12.920 --> 00:08:18.480
- I opened a dialogue with Gorkon.
Chancellor of the Klingon High Council.

92
00:08:18.720 --> 00:08:22.400
He proposes to
commence negotiations at once.

93
00:08:22.640 --> 00:08:25.200
Negotiations for what?

94
00:08:25.440 --> 00:08:28.960
The dismantling of our space stations
and bases along the Neutral Zone. -

95
00:08:29.200 --> 00:08:35.040
- an end to 70 years of hostility.
which the Klingons can no longer afford.

96
00:08:35.280 --> 00:08:39.120
Bill. are we talking about
mothballing the Starfleet?

97
00:08:39.880 --> 00:08:44.160
Our exploration and scientific programs
would be unaffected. but...

98
00:08:44.400 --> 00:08:45.720
I must protest!

99
00:08:45.960 --> 00:08:49.960
To offer Klingons safe haven
within Federation space is suicide.

100
00:08:50.200 --> 00:08:53.120
Klingons would become
the alien trash of the galaxy.

101
00:08:53.360 --> 00:08:54.800
If we dismantle the fleet. -

102
00:08:55.040 --> 00:08:59.440
- we'd be defenceless before
an aggressive species on our territory.

103
00:08:59.680 --> 00:09:03.400
The opportunity here is
to bring them to their knees.

104
00:09:03.640 --> 00:09:07.360
Then we'll be in a better position
to dictate terms.

105
00:09:08.120 --> 00:09:11.160
- Sir...
- Captain Kirk?

106
00:09:11.400 --> 00:09:15.280
The Klingons
have never been trustworthy.

107
00:09:15.520 --> 00:09:19.480
I agree with Admiral Cartwright.
This is a terrifying idea.

108
00:09:19.720 --> 00:09:23.920
It is imperative that we act now
to support the Gorkon initiative. -

109
00:09:24.160 --> 00:09:27.080
- lest more conservative elements
persuade his empire -

110
00:09:27.320 --> 00:09:30.720
- that it's better to attempt
a military solution and die fighting.

111
00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:33.960
You. Captain Kirk.
are to be our first olive branch.

112
00:09:35.600 --> 00:09:40.160
We are to rendezvous with the vessel
which is bringing Gorkon to Earth -

113
00:09:40.400 --> 00:09:43.080
- and to escort him safely through
Federation space.

114
00:09:43.680 --> 00:09:45.240
Me?

115
00:09:45.480 --> 00:09:51.040
There are Klingons who feel the same
about the peace treaty as yourself. -

116
00:09:51.280 --> 00:09:54.560
- but they'll think twice about attacking
the Enterprise under your command.

117
00:09:54.800 --> 00:09:57.920
I have personally vouched for you
in this matter.

118
00:09:58.560 --> 00:10:01.600
You have personally vouched...?

119
00:10:02.520 --> 00:10:07.120
You will extend Chancellor Gorkon
full diplomatic courtesy. Captain.

120
00:10:07.360 --> 00:10:11.200
- A full Ambassador is better equipped...
- If there's no further business...

121
00:10:11.960 --> 00:10:15.680
...I wish you and your crew Godspeed.
Thank you. ladies and gentlemen.

122
00:10:15.920 --> 00:10:18.840
I remind you this meeting is classified.

123
00:10:24.760 --> 00:10:28.920
I don't know whether to
congratulate you or not. Jim.

124
00:10:29.160 --> 00:10:31.120
I wouldn't.

125
00:10:34.280 --> 00:10:36.120
We volunteered?

126
00:10:36.360 --> 00:10:41.080
There's an old Vulcan proverb.
"Only Nixon could go to China."

127
00:10:42.360 --> 00:10:45.040
How could you vouch for me?

128
00:10:45.280 --> 00:10:49.760
- That's arrogant presumption.
- My father requested that I open...

129
00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:55.200
I know your father is the Vulcan
Ambassador. but you know how I feel.

130
00:10:56.880 --> 00:10:59.160
- They're animals.
- Jim...

131
00:10:59.400 --> 00:11:04.360
- There is an historic opportunity here.
- Don't believe them! Don't trust them.

132
00:11:05.080 --> 00:11:07.640
- They're dying.
- Let them die.

133
00:11:10.560 --> 00:11:15.600
Has it occurred to you that this crew is
due to stand down in three months?

134
00:11:15.840 --> 00:11:18.320
We've done our bit for king and country.

135
00:11:19.320 --> 00:11:21.120
You should have trusted me.

136
00:11:27.040 --> 00:11:30.760
Control. this is S-D 103.
approach to Space dock. Over.

137
00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:38.200
You are clear to deliver Captain Kirk
and party to N.C.C. 1701 Alpha.

138
00:11:43.120 --> 00:11:46.440
- Captain on the bridge!
- As you were. Lieutenant?

139
00:11:46.680 --> 00:11:51.120
Val'eris. sir. We were told you needed
a helmsman. so I volunteered.

140
00:11:52.120 --> 00:11:54.160
It is agreeable to see you again.

141
00:11:54.400 --> 00:11:58.440
She was the first Vulcan to graduate
at the top of her class at the Academy.

142
00:11:58.680 --> 00:12:01.800
- You must be very proud.
- I don't believe so. sir.

143
00:12:02.040 --> 00:12:03.440
She's a Vulcan. alright.

144
00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:07.440
Let's get this over with.
Departure stations.

145
00:12:07.680 --> 00:12:11.600
- Scotty? Did you find the engine room?
- Right where I left it.

146
00:12:11.840 --> 00:12:14.520
Stand by.
Uhura. get me the dock master.

147
00:12:14.760 --> 00:12:16.280
Control tower reading. sir.

148
00:12:16.800 --> 00:12:21.040
Control. this is Enterprise
requesting permission to depart.

149
00:12:21.280 --> 00:12:25.960
This is Control. Permission to depart
granted. 30 seconds for port gates.

150
00:12:26.200 --> 00:12:30.400
- Clear all moorings.
- Awaiting port gates from this mark.

151
00:12:30.640 --> 00:12:33.280
- All lines clear.
- Aft thrusters.

152
00:12:33.520 --> 00:12:36.680
Thank you. Lieutenant.
1 quarter impulse power.

153
00:12:36.920 --> 00:12:41.640
Captain. regulations specify
thrusters only while in space dock.

154
00:12:46.200 --> 00:12:47.560
Jim...

155
00:12:49.840 --> 00:12:51.920
You heard the order. Lieutenant.

156
00:12:52.880 --> 00:12:55.080
Aye. sir.

157
00:13:26.160 --> 00:13:29.680
Captain's log. Stardate 9522.6.

158
00:13:29.920 --> 00:13:35.080
I've never trusted Klingons.
and I never will.

159
00:13:38.320 --> 00:13:42.000
I can never forgive them for
the death of my boy.

160
00:13:43.320 --> 00:13:50.280
To escort the Chancellor of the Klingon
High Council to a peace summit -

161
00:13:50.520 --> 00:13:53.200
- is problematic. at best.

162
00:13:56.160 --> 00:14:00.800
Spock says this could be an historic
occasion. I'd like to believe him.

163
00:14:01.040 --> 00:14:05.840
But how on Earth can history get past
people like me?

164
00:14:07.240 --> 00:14:10.440
- Sorry.
- You could have knocked.

165
00:14:10.680 --> 00:14:15.800
We are almost at the rendezvous. sir.
I thought that you would like to know.

166
00:14:19.880 --> 00:14:24.240
Permission to speak freely. sir.
It is an honour to serve with you.

167
00:14:29.760 --> 00:14:32.320
You piloted well out of space dock.
Lieutenant.

168
00:14:33.240 --> 00:14:35.320
I've always wanted to try that.

169
00:14:45.320 --> 00:14:47.640
You've done well. Val'eris.

170
00:14:47.880 --> 00:14:53.680
As your sponsor at the Academy I've
followed your career with satisfaction.

171
00:14:53.920 --> 00:14:58.080
And as a Vulcan.
you have exceeded my expectations.

172
00:14:59.760 --> 00:15:03.000
I do not understand this representation.

173
00:15:03.240 --> 00:15:07.600
It's a depiction
from ancient Earth mythology.

174
00:15:07.840 --> 00:15:09.200
"The expulsion from Paradise."

175
00:15:09.440 --> 00:15:15.400
- Why keep it in your quarters?
- To remind me that all things end.

176
00:15:19.960 --> 00:15:25.480
It is of endings that I wish to speak.

177
00:15:25.720 --> 00:15:28.920
Sir. I address you
as a kindred intellect.

178
00:15:30.040 --> 00:15:32.680
Do you not recognise...

179
00:15:32.920 --> 00:15:36.440
...that a turning point has been reached
in the affairs of the Federation?

180
00:15:38.600 --> 00:15:44.040
History is replete with turning points.
You must have faith.

181
00:15:44.280 --> 00:15:48.200
- Faith?
- The universe will unfold as it should.

182
00:15:49.280 --> 00:15:54.920
- Is that logical? Surely we must...
- Logic. logic. logic.

183
00:15:55.160 --> 00:16:02.200
Logic is the beginning of wisdom.
Val'eris. Not the end.

184
00:16:03.120 --> 00:16:06.720
This will be my final voyage on board
this vessel as a member of her crew.

185
00:16:10.320 --> 00:16:14.160
Nature abhors a vacuum.

186
00:16:14.400 --> 00:16:17.440
I intend you to replace me.

187
00:16:25.200 --> 00:16:28.120
I could only succeed you. sir.

188
00:16:32.320 --> 00:16:34.880
Now hear this.
All offiicers to the bridge.

189
00:16:35.120 --> 00:16:39.160
Klingon battle cruiser off the port bow.
All Officers to the bridge.

190
00:16:55.200 --> 00:16:57.480
Captain on the bridge!

191
00:17:10.560 --> 00:17:12.800
Shall we raise our shields. Captain?

192
00:17:14.480 --> 00:17:16.680
I've never been this close.

193
00:17:18.680 --> 00:17:21.880
The Chancellor is undoubtedly
awaiting our signal.

194
00:17:30.680 --> 00:17:33.640
- Uhura. hailing frequencies.
- Aye. sir.

195
00:17:33.880 --> 00:17:36.040
Right standard rudder.
Bring us alongside.

196
00:17:36.280 --> 00:17:39.000
Right standard rudder.
Z plus 5 degrees.

197
00:17:39.240 --> 00:17:41.800
Channel is open. Captain.

198
00:17:42.040 --> 00:17:46.040
This is the Starship Enterprise.
Captain James T. Kirk commanding.

199
00:17:46.640 --> 00:17:52.120
This is Kronos One.
I am Chancellor Gorkon.

200
00:17:56.240 --> 00:18:01.360
We've been ordered to escort you
to your meeting on Earth.

201
00:18:01.560 --> 00:18:02.920
Thank you.

202
00:18:03.720 --> 00:18:09.000
Would you and your party care to dine
this evening aboard the Enterprise -

203
00:18:09.240 --> 00:18:11.640
- as guests of
the United Federation of Planets?

204
00:18:11.880 --> 00:18:16.480
We would be delighted to accept
your gracious invitation.

205
00:18:18.640 --> 00:18:21.720
We'll make arrangements to have you
beamed aboard at 19:30 hours.

206
00:18:22.320 --> 00:18:24.160
I shall look forward to that.

207
00:18:31.360 --> 00:18:33.280
I hope you're happy.

208
00:18:33.520 --> 00:18:37.120
Captain! There is a supply of
Romulan ale aboard.

209
00:18:37.360 --> 00:18:40.360
It might make
the evening pass more... smoothly.

210
00:18:40.960 --> 00:18:43.360
Officer thinking. Lieutenant.

211
00:18:45.480 --> 00:18:47.200
Guess who's coming to dinner.

212
00:18:58.680 --> 00:19:00.560
Energize.

213
00:19:32.800 --> 00:19:34.840
- Chancellor Gorkon.
- Captain Kirk.

214
00:19:35.080 --> 00:19:37.960
May I present Captain Spock.
whom I believe you know.

215
00:19:38.200 --> 00:19:43.040
Captain. face to face at last.
You have my thanks.

216
00:19:43.280 --> 00:19:46.320
Chancellor.

217
00:19:46.560 --> 00:19:48.520
Gentlemen.

218
00:19:48.760 --> 00:19:51.600
This is my daughter. Azetbur...

219
00:19:55.040 --> 00:20:00.160
My military advisor. Brigadier Kerla...

220
00:20:00.360 --> 00:20:03.920
General Chang.
my chief of staff.

221
00:20:04.160 --> 00:20:07.200
I have so wanted to meet you. Captain.

222
00:20:08.320 --> 00:20:13.720
- I'm not sure how to take that.
- Sincere admiration. Kirk.

223
00:20:13.960 --> 00:20:16.920
From one warrior to another.

224
00:20:18.400 --> 00:20:21.080
Right...

225
00:20:22.560 --> 00:20:26.920
This way. You might enjoy a brief tour.

226
00:20:43.240 --> 00:20:45.680
- They all look alike.
- What about that smell?

227
00:20:45.920 --> 00:20:50.640
You know only top of the line models
can even talk...

228
00:20:54.360 --> 00:20:56.920
- You men have work?
- Yes. ma'am.

229
00:20:57.120 --> 00:20:59.200
Then snap to it.

230
00:21:36.680 --> 00:21:38.400
I offer a toast.

231
00:21:39.200 --> 00:21:42.360
The undiscovered country.

232
00:21:44.680 --> 00:21:47.480
- The future.
- The undiscovered country.

233
00:21:47.720 --> 00:21:49.760
Hamlet. act 3. scene 1 .

234
00:21:50.000 --> 00:21:54.040
You have not experienced Shake-
speare until you've read him in Klingon.

235
00:22:04.560 --> 00:22:08.440
Captain Kirk.
I thought Romulan ale was illegal.

236
00:22:08.680 --> 00:22:12.400
An advantage of being 1.000 light
years from Federation headquarters.

237
00:22:13.440 --> 00:22:17.160
To you. Chancellor Gorkon.
One of the architects of our future.

238
00:22:17.400 --> 00:22:18.880
Chancellor!

239
00:22:21.320 --> 00:22:24.480
Perhaps we are looking at
something of that future here.

240
00:22:27.440 --> 00:22:34.200
Tell me. Captain Kirk. Would you
be willing to give up Starfleet?

241
00:22:38.040 --> 00:22:44.120
The Captain feels that Starfleet's
mission has always been one of peace.

242
00:22:47.320 --> 00:22:51.200
I wouldn't dispute my first officer.
Starfleet has always been...

243
00:22:51.440 --> 00:22:56.240
There's no need to mince words.
In space. all warriors are cold warriors.

244
00:22:58.640 --> 00:23:03.560
General.
are you fond of... Shakespeare?

245
00:23:04.360 --> 00:23:09.040
We believe all planets have a sovereign
claim to inalienable human rights.

246
00:23:09.280 --> 00:23:14.040
"Inalien..."
If you could only hear yourselves.

247
00:23:14.280 --> 00:23:19.400
"Human rights."
Why. the very name is racist.

248
00:23:19.600 --> 00:23:23.240
The Federation is
a "homo sapiens only" club.

249
00:23:23.480 --> 00:23:26.200
Present company excepted. of course.

250
00:23:26.440 --> 00:23:31.640
We know where this is leading -
the annihilation of our culture.

251
00:23:31.880 --> 00:23:35.120
That's not true. No!

252
00:23:35.360 --> 00:23:40.840
"To be or not to be"... That is the
question which preoccupies our people.

253
00:23:41.080 --> 00:23:44.280
- We need breathing room.
- Earth. Hitler. 1938.

254
00:23:46.280 --> 00:23:48.200
I beg your pardon.

255
00:23:51.960 --> 00:23:53.800
Well...

256
00:23:56.080 --> 00:23:58.960
I see we have a long way to go.

257
00:23:59.560 --> 00:24:03.000
We must do this again sometime.

258
00:24:06.120 --> 00:24:11.280
You don't trust me. do you?
I don't blame you.

259
00:24:12.880 --> 00:24:15.320
If there is to be a brave new world. -

260
00:24:15.560 --> 00:24:21.200
- our generation is going to have
the hardest time living in it.

261
00:24:24.040 --> 00:24:28.200
- Captain Spock.
- Chancellor. Madam.

262
00:24:28.440 --> 00:24:30.280
Captain.

263
00:24:30.520 --> 00:24:33.000
Well. most kind.

264
00:24:33.240 --> 00:24:38.480
Parting is such sweet sorrow.
Hmm. Captain?

265
00:24:39.320 --> 00:24:43.120
"Have we not heard the chimes
at midnight?"

266
00:25:05.840 --> 00:25:08.400
Thank God!

267
00:25:08.600 --> 00:25:13.960
- Did you see the way they ate?
- Terrible table manners.

268
00:25:14.200 --> 00:25:18.200
I doubt our own behaviour will distinguish
us in the annals of diplomacy.

269
00:25:18.440 --> 00:25:22.800
I'm going to sleep this off. Is there any
other way we can screw up tonight?

270
00:25:23.040 --> 00:25:26.920
I'm going to go find
a pot of black coffee.

271
00:25:40.680 --> 00:25:46.920
The Enterprise hosted
Chancellor Gorkon to dinner last night.

272
00:25:47.160 --> 00:25:51.480
Our manners
weren't exactly Emily Post.

273
00:25:51.720 --> 00:25:58.760
To the galley - Romulan ale no longer
to be served at diplomatic functions.

274
00:25:59.400 --> 00:26:04.240
Captain Kirk. will you please
join me on the bridge? Captain Kirk?

275
00:26:10.280 --> 00:26:12.280
- Captain.
- What is it?

276
00:26:12.520 --> 00:26:15.280
- I find this curious.
- Spock. I'm really tired.

277
00:26:15.520 --> 00:26:20.080
We are reading an enormous amount of
neutron radiation.

278
00:26:20.320 --> 00:26:24.240
- Where?
- It appears to emanate from us.

279
00:26:24.480 --> 00:26:26.360
The Enterprise?

280
00:26:28.240 --> 00:26:32.400
Val'eris. do you know anything about
a radiation surge? Chekov?

281
00:26:33.280 --> 00:26:36.520
Only the size of my head.

282
00:26:37.160 --> 00:26:38.960
I know what you mean.

283
00:26:53.320 --> 00:26:56.640
- What's happened?
- We've fired on the Chancellor's ship.

284
00:26:56.880 --> 00:26:59.920
Torpedo room!
Please confirm. have we fired?

285
00:27:01.440 --> 00:27:03.520
- Uhura. monitor.
- Aye. sir.

286
00:27:03.760 --> 00:27:08.000
- Direct hit.
- Confirmed. sir.

287
00:27:18.360 --> 00:27:19.920
We've lost gravity!

288
00:27:33.960 --> 00:27:35.480
We are betrayed!

289
00:27:35.720 --> 00:27:39.400
This is the bridge. Do you read me?

290
00:27:39.640 --> 00:27:44.880
- Did we fire those torpedoes?
- Negative. We're still fully loaded.

291
00:28:02.840 --> 00:28:05.400
Find Chang.

292
00:28:11.720 --> 00:28:14.720
Unable to confirm or deny
firing the torpedoes.

293
00:28:14.960 --> 00:28:17.320
- Hailing frequencies.
- Aye. sir.

294
00:28:17.560 --> 00:28:20.840
Kronos One. this is Enterprise.
Do you read?

295
00:29:25.240 --> 00:29:30.440
It's very hard to make out. There's been
weapons firing and a lot of shouting.

296
00:29:30.920 --> 00:29:35.000
- She's still listing.
- She's spinning out of control.

297
00:29:53.120 --> 00:29:56.880
Restoring auxiliary gravity...

298
00:30:06.680 --> 00:30:10.280
Have you not
a shred of decency in you. Kirk?

299
00:30:10.520 --> 00:30:16.240
We come in peace.
and you blatantly defy that peace.

300
00:30:16.480 --> 00:30:18.760
For that.
I shall blow you out of the stars.

301
00:30:21.480 --> 00:30:25.040
- We haven't fired.
- Captain...

302
00:30:25.280 --> 00:30:28.760
According to our data banks.
we have. Twice...

303
00:30:29.000 --> 00:30:30.760
Captain. they're coming about.

304
00:30:37.480 --> 00:30:40.080
- They're preparing to fire.
- Shields up. Captain?

305
00:30:40.320 --> 00:30:43.640
- Captain. our shields.
- Shields up. Captain?

306
00:30:45.840 --> 00:30:48.320
Signal our surrender.

307
00:30:48.400 --> 00:30:49.720
We surrender!

308
00:30:50.960 --> 00:30:55.640
- This is Enterprise. We surrender.
- If they fire. with our shields down...

309
00:30:55.720 --> 00:30:59.680
- ...we will not be able to respond.
- Repeat. Enterprise surrenders.

310
00:31:03.000 --> 00:31:06.640
- Are we firing torpedoes?
- I wish I knew.

311
00:31:06.880 --> 00:31:11.000
- I'm going aboard. Spock. take the con.
- I involved you. I will go.

312
00:31:11.240 --> 00:31:17.280
No. I'll go. We'll not be the instigators
of war on the eve of universal peace.

313
00:31:17.520 --> 00:31:20.080
I'm going too. they may need a doctor.

314
00:31:20.320 --> 00:31:24.840
Uhura. tell them we're coming.
and tell them we're unarmed.

315
00:31:29.760 --> 00:31:33.000
- Have you lost your mind?!
- I don't understand what's happened.

316
00:31:33.240 --> 00:31:36.320
We're here to help.

317
00:31:36.560 --> 00:31:38.920
Follow me.

318
00:32:02.240 --> 00:32:06.680
- Chancellor Gorkon.
- My God! What has happened here?

319
00:32:06.920 --> 00:32:10.520
- You dare to feign ignorance?
- What happened?

320
00:32:10.760 --> 00:32:14.800
With a direct torpedo hit.
you crippled our gravitational field -

321
00:32:15.040 --> 00:32:19.800
- and two of your Starfleet crew beamed
aboard wearing magnetic boots.

322
00:32:20.040 --> 00:32:23.160
- Aren't you carrying a surgeon?
- We were until this disgrace.

323
00:32:23.400 --> 00:32:25.720
Then for god's sake. let me help.

324
00:32:36.680 --> 00:32:42.080
I've got a pulse - we can move him.
I need light. Put him on the table.

325
00:32:50.120 --> 00:32:54.040
Hold him! Hold him while I stabilize him.

326
00:32:59.760 --> 00:33:02.240
I said hold him!

327
00:33:05.440 --> 00:33:06.840
Sweet Jesus.

328
00:33:07.080 --> 00:33:10.000
- Can you...?
- I don't even know his anatomy.

329
00:33:14.520 --> 00:33:16.760
- His wounds are not closing.
- He's killing him!

330
00:33:22.400 --> 00:33:25.480
He's gone into
some kind of damned arrest.

331
00:33:29.320 --> 00:33:31.680
Come on. dammit! Come on!

332
00:33:36.400 --> 00:33:38.400
He's not responding.

333
00:33:56.560 --> 00:34:00.160
Don't let it end this way. Captain.

334
00:34:34.840 --> 00:34:40.680
Under article 184 of your
Interstellar Law...

335
00:34:40.920 --> 00:34:43.160
...I'm placing you under arrest.

336
00:34:43.400 --> 00:34:48.640
You're charged with assassinating
the Chancellor of the High Council.

337
00:34:48.880 --> 00:34:51.600
He tried to save him.

338
00:34:57.120 --> 00:35:00.160
They've been arrested.

339
00:35:00.400 --> 00:35:04.040
Mr Spock. we've got to do something.

340
00:35:04.280 --> 00:35:07.280
I assume command of this ship
as of 02:30 hours.

341
00:35:07.520 --> 00:35:13.600
Commander Uhura. notify Starfleet
headquarters and request instructions.

342
00:35:13.840 --> 00:35:17.680
We cannot allow them
to be taken to Kronos as prisoners.

343
00:35:17.920 --> 00:35:22.320
Opening fire will not retrieve them.
and we must avoid an armed conflict.

344
00:35:22.560 --> 00:35:24.800
We will be able to follow
the Captain's movements.

345
00:35:25.040 --> 00:35:28.080
- How did you achieve this?
- Time is precious.

346
00:35:28.320 --> 00:35:31.520
We must piece together
what happened here tonight.

347
00:35:31.760 --> 00:35:35.160
According to our data bank.
this ship fired those torpedoes.

348
00:35:35.400 --> 00:35:39.800
- No way!
- I sympathize. but we need evidence.

349
00:35:40.040 --> 00:35:43.360
Please accompany me.

350
00:35:43.600 --> 00:35:47.360
And if we cannot piece together
what happened? What then. sir?

351
00:35:47.600 --> 00:35:51.600
In that case. Mr Chekov. it resides in
the purview of the diplomats.

352
00:35:53.560 --> 00:35:57.400
The Chancellor of
the High Council is dead!

353
00:35:57.640 --> 00:36:00.480
The result of an unprovoked attack -

354
00:36:00.720 --> 00:36:06.240
- while he travelled to see you under
a flag of truce on a mission of peace!

355
00:36:06.480 --> 00:36:09.600
Captain Kirk
was legally arrested for the crime.

356
00:36:09.840 --> 00:36:14.720
He and Dr. McCoy boarded
Kronos One of their own free will.

357
00:36:14.960 --> 00:36:19.880
- None of these facts are in dispute.
- I have ordered an investigation.

358
00:36:20.840 --> 00:36:22.880
- In the meantime...
- In the meantime...

359
00:36:23.120 --> 00:36:29.320
...we expect the Federation to abide by
the articles of Interstellar Law.

360
00:36:29.560 --> 00:36:34.280
Kirk and Dr. McCoy will stand trial for
the assassination of Chancellor Gorkon.

361
00:36:34.520 --> 00:36:38.920
Out of the question. Ambassador
Sarek. can we get them extradited?

362
00:36:39.560 --> 00:36:44.360
I share a measure of
personal responsibility in this matter. -

363
00:36:44.600 --> 00:36:48.720
- but I am obliged to confirm my
esteemed colleagues legal interpretation.

364
00:36:48.960 --> 00:36:52.240
What is the position of
the Romulan government?

365
00:36:53.680 --> 00:36:55.880
I must concur with my colleagues.

366
00:36:56.120 --> 00:37:01.360
You can't believe that Kirk assassinated
the Chancellor of the High Council.

367
00:37:01.600 --> 00:37:05.880
Mr President.
I don't know what to believe.

368
00:37:06.680 --> 00:37:08.880
I'm waiting for your answer. sir.

369
00:37:11.120 --> 00:37:15.040
This President is not above the law.

370
00:37:19.840 --> 00:37:22.480
Report back on the double.
Do you read?

371
00:37:22.720 --> 00:37:28.000
- We're to report back at once.
- We can't abandon Kirk and McCoy.

372
00:37:28.240 --> 00:37:33.440
400 years ago. on Earth. workers
who felt their livelyhood threatened -

373
00:37:33.680 --> 00:37:38.960
- flung their wooden shoes called
"sabots" into the machines to stop them.

374
00:37:41.120 --> 00:37:44.640
Hence the word "sabotage".

375
00:37:47.160 --> 00:37:52.080
We experience technical malfunction.
All back-up systems inoperative.

376
00:37:52.320 --> 00:37:55.480
Excellent. I mean... too bad.

377
00:37:56.800 --> 00:38:02.520
Mr President. I have been named
chancellorin my father's place.

378
00:38:02.760 --> 00:38:06.720
Madam Chancellor.
you have my condolences on your loss.

379
00:38:06.960 --> 00:38:10.760
I assure you
that this shameful deed will not...

380
00:38:11.000 --> 00:38:16.000
Let us come to the point. You want
this conference to go forward.

381
00:38:16.240 --> 00:38:19.440
I will attend in one week.
on one condition.

382
00:38:19.680 --> 00:38:25.840
We will not extradite the prisoners.
and you will not attempt to rescue them.

383
00:38:26.080 --> 00:38:29.920
We would consider any such attempt
an act of war.

384
00:38:30.160 --> 00:38:32.160
We hope you'll be our guest
here on Earth.

385
00:38:32.400 --> 00:38:37.160
After recent events. you will
understand if I prefer a neutral site.

386
00:38:37.400 --> 00:38:42.440
And in the interest of security. let us
keep the location secret for now.

387
00:38:42.680 --> 00:38:45.720
As you wish. Madam Chancellor.

388
00:38:47.000 --> 00:38:50.200
Attack them now. while we still can.

389
00:38:50.440 --> 00:38:54.000
Attack or be slaves in their world.

390
00:38:57.440 --> 00:39:01.040
We can take whole by force.
what they propose to divide.

391
00:39:01.880 --> 00:39:06.320
War is obsolete. General.

392
00:39:06.560 --> 00:39:11.600
As we are in danger of becoming.

393
00:39:11.840 --> 00:39:17.200
Better to die on our feet
than live on our knees.

394
00:39:17.440 --> 00:39:20.440
That wasn't what my father wanted.

395
00:39:20.680 --> 00:39:24.040
Your father was killed
for what he wanted.

396
00:39:24.760 --> 00:39:28.800
The peace process will go forward.

397
00:39:29.560 --> 00:39:31.240
Kirk...

398
00:39:34.560 --> 00:39:39.160
Kirk will pay for my father's death.

399
00:39:43.494 --> 00:39:47.533
Kirk. Kirk. Kirk. Kirk...

400
00:40:09.101 --> 00:40:10.971
It's a damn show trial.

401
00:40:21.521 --> 00:40:25.995
The Enterprise fired on Kronos One
without provocation.

402
00:40:26.263 --> 00:40:27.999
The Chancellor and his advisors...

403
00:40:28.232 --> 00:40:30.802
...having been lulled into
a false sense of security -

404
00:40:31.036 --> 00:40:34.408
- by an invitation to a dinner
aboard Captain Kirk's vessel -

405
00:40:34.643 --> 00:40:38.582
- at precisely 19:30 hours
that same evening.

406
00:40:39.082 --> 00:40:41.186
Call your first witness.

407
00:40:41.420 --> 00:40:44.825
After the first shot
we lost our gravitational field.

408
00:40:45.059 --> 00:40:47.095
I was weightless and couldn't function.

409
00:40:47.329 --> 00:40:50.100
Then two Starfleet crewmen
came towards me.

410
00:40:50.334 --> 00:40:52.939
Or perhaps
they merely wore Starfleet uniforms.

411
00:40:53.172 --> 00:40:56.009
That remark is speculative.
I move that it be stricken.

412
00:40:56.277 --> 00:41:00.116
We're interested in facts. not theories.

413
00:41:00.784 --> 00:41:05.758
If the gravitational unit was not
functioning. how could they walk?

414
00:41:05.992 --> 00:41:08.196
They appeared to be wearing
magnetic boots.

415
00:41:10.866 --> 00:41:15.140
- Gravity boots...?
- Dr. McCoy.

416
00:41:15.407 --> 00:41:19.080
Would you be so good as to tell me -

417
00:41:19.313 --> 00:41:23.053
- what is your current medical status?

418
00:41:23.287 --> 00:41:26.559
Aside from a touch of arthritis.
I'd say pretty good.

419
00:41:33.436 --> 00:41:35.740
You have a singular wit. Doctor.

420
00:41:35.973 --> 00:41:40.281
For 27 years I've been surgeon
aboard the U.S.S. Enterprise.

421
00:41:40.514 --> 00:41:45.455
In three months I stand down.

422
00:41:45.689 --> 00:41:47.358
You know...

423
00:41:47.625 --> 00:41:52.466
I believe that you consumed rather
a generous amount of Romulan ale -

424
00:41:52.700 --> 00:41:55.004
- in the officers mess
on the night in question.

425
00:41:55.271 --> 00:41:57.141
- Objection.
- Sustained.

426
00:41:57.374 --> 00:42:00.646
We all did. All of us.
That doesn't mean...

427
00:42:00.913 --> 00:42:06.322
Was Chancellor Gorkon alive
when you first examined him?

428
00:42:06.556 --> 00:42:07.791
Barely.

429
00:42:08.024 --> 00:42:11.764
Now be careful. Doctor.
Have you ever in your past -

430
00:42:11.998 --> 00:42:15.904
- saved patients as barely alive as he?

431
00:42:16.137 --> 00:42:19.076
I didn't have the medical knowledge
I needed for Klingon anatomy.

432
00:42:19.309 --> 00:42:22.481
- I see.
- You where there.

433
00:42:22.715 --> 00:42:27.689
You say you are due for retirement.
May I ask. do your hands shake?

434
00:42:27.923 --> 00:42:29.792
- Objection!
- I was nervous.

435
00:42:31.930 --> 00:42:34.935
No. You were incompetent.

436
00:42:37.672 --> 00:42:39.875
You were incompetent!

437
00:42:40.110 --> 00:42:43.915
Whether deliberately or as a result of
age combined with drink.

438
00:42:44.182 --> 00:42:48.757
- The court will have to determine.
- My God. man. I tried to save him!

439
00:42:49.858 --> 00:42:51.762
I tried to save him.

440
00:42:53.598 --> 00:42:57.137
I was desperate to save him.

441
00:42:57.370 --> 00:43:01.610
He was the last best hope
in the Universe for peace.

442
00:43:01.844 --> 00:43:04.448
The witness is excused.

443
00:43:07.620 --> 00:43:13.195
There we have it. citizens. We have
established the particulars of the crime.

444
00:43:13.430 --> 00:43:17.836
And now we come to the architect of
this tragic affair.

445
00:43:18.404 --> 00:43:23.178
James Tiberius Kirk.

446
00:43:25.082 --> 00:43:28.520
What would your favourite author say.
Captain?

447
00:43:28.754 --> 00:43:32.960
"Let us sit upon the ground and tell
sad stories of the death of kings."

448
00:43:33.194 --> 00:43:36.366
Tell us your sad story. Kirk.

449
00:43:36.599 --> 00:43:41.440
Tell us that you planned to take
revenge for the death of your son.

450
00:43:41.674 --> 00:43:43.377
- That's not true.
- Objection!

451
00:43:43.611 --> 00:43:48.351
Captain Kirk has not been identified
as the assassin.

452
00:43:48.619 --> 00:43:54.561
I offer into the record this excerpt
from the Captain's personal log.

453
00:43:55.196 --> 00:44:00.338
I've never trusted Klingons.
and I never will.

454
00:44:00.571 --> 00:44:03.777
I've never been able to forgive them
for the death of my boy.

455
00:44:07.482 --> 00:44:09.819
Again! Again!

456
00:44:10.053 --> 00:44:13.324
I've never trusted Klingons.
and I never will.

457
00:44:14.060 --> 00:44:17.899
I've never been able to forgive them
for the death of my boy.

458
00:44:20.937 --> 00:44:23.742
Are those your words?

459
00:44:26.145 --> 00:44:28.549
Those words were spoken by me.

460
00:44:32.222 --> 00:44:36.195
Objection! My client's political views
are not on trial.

461
00:44:36.428 --> 00:44:42.004
On the contrary. Captain Kirk's views
are at the very heart of the matter.

462
00:44:42.238 --> 00:44:48.214
His record shows him to be an
insubordinate. unprincipled opportunist -

463
00:44:48.447 --> 00:44:51.552
- with a history of violating the chain of
command whenever it suited him.

464
00:44:51.819 --> 00:44:53.055
Continue.

465
00:44:53.288 --> 00:44:57.462
The record shows that Captain Kirk
once held the rank of Admiral -

466
00:44:57.696 --> 00:45:02.303
- and he was broken for taking matters
into his own hands.

467
00:45:02.537 --> 00:45:07.178
Do you deny being demoted for
these charges. Answer me now!

468
00:45:07.412 --> 00:45:09.848
- I cannot deny it.
- You were demoted?

469
00:45:10.082 --> 00:45:14.055
- For insubordination?
- On occasion. I have disobeyed orders.

470
00:45:14.289 --> 00:45:17.327
Were you obeying
or disobeying orders -

471
00:45:17.594 --> 00:45:20.131
- when you arranged the assassination
of Chancellor Gorkon?

472
00:45:20.331 --> 00:45:22.836
I didn't know about it
until we boarded the ship.

473
00:45:23.069 --> 00:45:27.610
You still deny the Enterprise
fired on Kronos One?

474
00:45:27.877 --> 00:45:31.917
And you still deny your men beamed
aboard and shot the Chancellor?

475
00:45:32.151 --> 00:45:36.458
I cannot confirm or deny
actions which I didn't witness.

476
00:45:36.724 --> 00:45:40.063
Are you aware
that as the captain of a ship. -

477
00:45:40.297 --> 00:45:43.870
- you are responsible for
the actions of your men?

478
00:45:46.407 --> 00:45:48.110
I am.

479
00:45:48.343 --> 00:45:53.919
If it's proved that members of your
crew carried out the assassination...

480
00:45:54.153 --> 00:45:56.890
- They're setting us up. Your Honours!
- Do not answer.

481
00:45:57.124 --> 00:46:01.631
Captain Kirk.
you will answer the question.

482
00:46:08.442 --> 00:46:11.580
As Captain...

483
00:46:11.814 --> 00:46:14.886
...I'm responsible for
the crew under my command.

484
00:46:18.491 --> 00:46:21.429
Your Honours. the state rests.

485
00:46:22.965 --> 00:46:26.237
Send to Commander Enterprise.

486
00:46:26.471 --> 00:46:30.210
"We stand ready to assist you.
Captain Sulu. U.S.S. Excelsior."

487
00:46:30.945 --> 00:46:37.756
It is the determination of this court that
the prisoners are guilty as charged.

488
00:46:48.639 --> 00:46:53.948
I wish to note for the record that
all the evidence is circumstantial.

489
00:46:54.182 --> 00:46:57.721
I beg the court to consider this
when pronouncing its sentence.

490
00:46:57.955 --> 00:46:59.457
So noted.

491
00:46:59.691 --> 00:47:03.430
Captain James T. Kirk.
Dr. Leonard McCoy.

492
00:47:03.697 --> 00:47:07.236
In the interest of fostering amity -

493
00:47:07.470 --> 00:47:13.646
- for the forthcoming peace talks.
the sentence of death is commuted.

494
00:47:20.490 --> 00:47:25.131
It is the judgement of this court -

495
00:47:25.365 --> 00:47:29.305
- that. without possibility
of reprieve or parole. -

496
00:47:29.539 --> 00:47:34.647
- you be taken from this place to
the dilithium mines -

497
00:47:34.847 --> 00:47:38.953
- on the penal asteroid of Rura Penthe.

498
00:47:39.621 --> 00:47:44.362
There to spend the rest of
your natural lives.

499
00:47:51.874 --> 00:47:54.545
Rura Penthe!

500
00:47:56.114 --> 00:48:00.154
Known throughout the galaxy as
the alien's graveyard.

501
00:48:00.387 --> 00:48:04.294
Better to kill them now
and get it over with.

502
00:48:23.525 --> 00:48:28.132
Lieutenant.
The torpedo hit once again. please.

503
00:48:32.907 --> 00:48:34.776
Hold.

504
00:48:35.443 --> 00:48:39.249
It is Enterprise. We fired.

505
00:48:39.517 --> 00:48:44.859
That is not possible! All weapons
visually accounted for. sir.

506
00:48:46.195 --> 00:48:47.730
An ancestor of mine maintained -

507
00:48:47.997 --> 00:48:53.539
- that if you eliminate the impossible.
whatever remains must be the truth.

508
00:48:53.773 --> 00:48:55.876
What does that mean?

509
00:48:56.110 --> 00:49:00.951
That if we cannot have fired
those torpedoes. someone else did.

510
00:49:01.185 --> 00:49:04.924
They didn't fire on themselves
and there are no other ships present.

511
00:49:05.158 --> 00:49:08.663
- There was a neutron surge.
- Not from us.

512
00:49:08.930 --> 00:49:13.671
A neutron surge that big
could only be produced by another ship.

513
00:49:13.905 --> 00:49:16.977
- Kronos One?
- Too far away.

514
00:49:17.210 --> 00:49:21.317
Very near us. Possibly beneath us.

515
00:49:21.551 --> 00:49:26.225
If there were a ship beneath us.
the Klingons would have seen it.

516
00:49:27.895 --> 00:49:30.298
Would they?

517
00:49:32.301 --> 00:49:36.909
- A Bird of Prey?
- A Bird of Prey.

518
00:49:38.544 --> 00:49:42.550
- Cloaked?
- They can't fired when they're cloaked.

519
00:49:42.784 --> 00:49:46.156
All things being equal. I would agree.

520
00:49:46.391 --> 00:49:50.230
However. things are not equal.
This one can.

521
00:49:50.997 --> 00:49:53.769
- We must inform Starfleet Command.
- Of what?

522
00:49:54.036 --> 00:49:58.476
A new weapon that's invisible?
They'll call us raving lunatics.

523
00:49:58.710 --> 00:50:03.284
They'll say we'll say anything
to exonerate the Captain.

524
00:50:03.518 --> 00:50:06.489
And they would be correct.
We have no evidence.

525
00:50:06.723 --> 00:50:09.728
Only a theory
which happens to fit the facts.

526
00:50:09.962 --> 00:50:14.435
Assuming you're right. Why would they
fire on their own President?

527
00:50:14.669 --> 00:50:16.606
Indeed.

528
00:50:16.839 --> 00:50:20.812
This ship will be searched
from bow to stern.

529
00:50:21.045 --> 00:50:24.919
I do not understand.
If there was a ship underneath us -

530
00:50:25.152 --> 00:50:29.158
- surely the assassins beamed aboard
from that vessel. not Enterprise.

531
00:50:29.392 --> 00:50:32.530
You're forgetting something.
Mr Chekov.

532
00:50:32.764 --> 00:50:36.537
According to our data banks.
this ship fired those torpedoes.

533
00:50:36.771 --> 00:50:39.141
If we did. the killers are here.

534
00:50:39.375 --> 00:50:43.382
If we did not.
whoever altered the data banks is here.

535
00:50:43.615 --> 00:50:47.988
In either case.
what we are looking for is here.

536
00:50:48.223 --> 00:50:52.496
- What are we looking for. sir?
- Lieutenant.

537
00:50:54.098 --> 00:50:56.068
Two pairs of gravity boots.

538
00:51:59.536 --> 00:52:02.808
This is the gulag Rura Penthe.

539
00:52:03.075 --> 00:52:09.986
There is no stockades.
no guard tower. no electronic frontier.

540
00:52:11.021 --> 00:52:14.427
Only a magnetic shield
prevents beaming.

541
00:52:14.660 --> 00:52:19.702
Punishment means exile
from prison to the surface.

542
00:52:20.603 --> 00:52:25.244
On the surface. nothing can survive.

543
00:52:28.883 --> 00:52:33.156
Work well. and you will be treated well.

544
00:52:33.390 --> 00:52:37.831
Work badly. and you will die.

545
00:53:59.762 --> 00:54:01.931
Oh. my God!

546
00:54:06.139 --> 00:54:11.047
The universal translator
has been confiscated.

547
00:54:11.313 --> 00:54:13.050
I'm sorry...?

548
00:54:17.290 --> 00:54:20.327
He's definitely on about something. Jim.

549
00:54:24.701 --> 00:54:26.137
If this is your spot. we'll move on.

550
00:54:27.673 --> 00:54:30.310
He wants your obedience to
the Brotherhood of Aliens.

551
00:54:30.545 --> 00:54:32.681
- He's got it.
- And your coat.

552
00:54:32.915 --> 00:54:34.751
I'm afraid not. It wouldn't fit.

553
00:54:49.808 --> 00:54:53.848
- Thanks.
- This will help keep you warm.

554
00:54:55.117 --> 00:55:00.793
- I'm Martia. You're Kirk and McCoy.
- How did you know that?

555
00:55:01.060 --> 00:55:03.196
We don't get many
presidential assassins.

556
00:55:03.463 --> 00:55:07.136
- We didn't kill Gorkon.
- Of course not.

557
00:55:07.370 --> 00:55:10.307
- But there's a reward for your death.
- That figures.

558
00:55:11.243 --> 00:55:12.845
We've been set up.

559
00:55:13.112 --> 00:55:16.184
Somebody up there
wants you out of the way.

560
00:55:23.462 --> 00:55:24.998
- Any progress?
- None.

561
00:55:25.231 --> 00:55:30.173
A crew of 300 are looking everywhere.
but the killers may still be among them.

562
00:55:30.440 --> 00:55:33.711
Surely they have disposed of
these boots by now.

563
00:55:33.945 --> 00:55:36.683
Would it not have been logical
to leave them on Gorkon's ship?

564
00:55:36.917 --> 00:55:41.825
Logic must give way to physics. Gravity
wasn't restored when they escaped.

565
00:55:42.058 --> 00:55:46.199
Without the boots. they would have
floated off the transporter pads.

566
00:55:46.432 --> 00:55:48.669
Why not simply vaporize them?

567
00:55:51.674 --> 00:55:53.477
Like this?

568
00:55:59.720 --> 00:56:05.762
As you know. no one can fire an
unauthorized phaser aboard a starship.

569
00:56:07.098 --> 00:56:11.038
Suppose. when they returned.
they threw the boots into the refuse.

570
00:56:11.305 --> 00:56:13.842
I'm having the refuse searched.

571
00:56:14.042 --> 00:56:19.685
If I'm correct. those boots will cling to
the killer's necks like Tiberian bats.

572
00:56:19.952 --> 00:56:24.627
They couldn't escape without them
nor throw them out the window.

573
00:56:24.860 --> 00:56:26.797
Those boots are here. Somewhere.

574
00:56:27.030 --> 00:56:32.940
- Did someone fire off a phaser?
- It's alright. It's nothing.

575
00:56:33.174 --> 00:56:37.413
Mr Spock. Starfleet is screaming for us
to return to port.

576
00:56:37.681 --> 00:56:40.585
- Who fired the...
- Ah. Mr Scott.

577
00:56:40.819 --> 00:56:45.159
I hear you have difficulty with the warp
drive. How long do you need for repair?

578
00:56:45.393 --> 00:56:48.031
There's nothing wrong
with the bloody thing.

579
00:56:48.264 --> 00:56:54.240
If we return to space dock. the killers
can dispose of their footwear -

580
00:56:54.475 --> 00:56:58.347
- and we will never see the Captain
or Dr. McCoy alive again.

581
00:56:58.614 --> 00:57:00.750
- It could take weeks.
- Thank you.

582
00:57:00.985 --> 00:57:04.757
Val'eris. inform Starfleet
our warp drive is inoperative.

583
00:57:04.991 --> 00:57:07.829
- A lie?
- An error.

584
00:57:08.563 --> 00:57:12.636
We have lost all contact
with the Captain and Dr. McCoy.

585
00:57:12.904 --> 00:57:16.676
Yes. at the moment they're surrounded
by a magnetic shield.

586
00:57:16.943 --> 00:57:22.318
But if I know the Captain.
he is deep into planning his escape.

587
00:57:44.353 --> 00:57:46.591
You've got him
where you want him. Jim!

588
00:58:37.572 --> 00:58:39.575
- Are you alright?
- I think so.

589
00:58:39.809 --> 00:58:43.615
- They'll respect you now.
- I was lucky that thing had knees.

590
00:58:43.849 --> 00:58:46.453
That was not his knee.

591
00:58:46.720 --> 00:58:50.259
Not everybody keep their genitals
in the same place. Captain.

592
00:58:50.493 --> 00:58:53.498
Anything you want to tell me?

593
00:58:53.731 --> 00:58:58.706
See what you can do for him. Let him
know we're not holding a grudge.

594
00:58:58.940 --> 00:59:02.512
Suppose he's holding a grudge?

595
00:59:02.745 --> 00:59:08.956
When whoever it is makes their move.
you won't be here to ask if he's the one.

596
00:59:12.194 --> 00:59:15.733
- Do you want to get out of here?
- There's got to be a way.

597
00:59:35.798 --> 00:59:39.004
Three months before retirement.
What a way to finish.

598
00:59:39.271 --> 00:59:43.144
- We're not finished.
- Speak for yourself.

599
00:59:43.378 --> 00:59:46.783
One day. one night... Kobayashi Maru!

600
00:59:47.017 --> 00:59:52.225
Bones! Are you afraid of the future?

601
00:59:52.458 --> 00:59:56.999
I believe that was the general idea
that I was trying to convey.

602
00:59:57.233 --> 01:00:02.374
- I don't mean this future.
- What is this - multiple choice?

603
01:00:02.641 --> 01:00:07.749
Some people are afraid...
of what might happen.

604
01:00:09.385 --> 01:00:13.826
- I was terrified.
- What terrified you. specifically?

605
01:00:19.970 --> 01:00:23.809
No more neutral zone.

606
01:00:24.042 --> 01:00:26.914
I was used to hating Klingons.

607
01:00:29.818 --> 01:00:33.858
It never even occurred to me
to take Gorkon at his words.

608
01:00:36.462 --> 01:00:41.771
- Spock was right.
- We all felt exactly the same.

609
01:00:42.005 --> 01:00:46.311
No. Somebody felt a lot worse.

610
01:00:48.047 --> 01:00:50.418
I'm beginning to understand why.

611
01:00:50.652 --> 01:00:53.823
If you've got any bright ideas.
now is the time.

612
01:00:54.057 --> 01:00:58.431
Time is the problem.
You and I are nothing.

613
01:00:58.665 --> 01:01:00.868
You heard the judge -
the peace conference is on again.

614
01:01:01.101 --> 01:01:05.075
Whoever killed Gorkon is bound to
attempt another assassination.

615
01:01:07.578 --> 01:01:09.615
Unless we can get out of here.

616
01:01:20.866 --> 01:01:25.908
It's me - Martia. Listen. No one has ever
escaped from Rura Penthe.

617
01:01:26.175 --> 01:01:29.413
- Except us.
- It is possible.

618
01:01:29.647 --> 01:01:31.616
I know how to get outside the shield.

619
01:01:31.851 --> 01:01:35.457
- How do we fit in?
- Getting outside the shield is easy.

620
01:01:35.690 --> 01:01:39.863
After that. you have to get us off the
surface before we freeze. Can you?

621
01:01:41.699 --> 01:01:45.640
- It's possible.
- I can't make it alone.

622
01:01:45.906 --> 01:01:49.345
You're the likeliest candidate
to come here for months.

623
01:01:49.579 --> 01:01:53.051
Candidate for what?

624
01:02:05.772 --> 01:02:10.312
Go to lift 7 in the morning
for mining duty. I'll see you there.

625
01:02:10.546 --> 01:02:12.916
Don't disappoint me.

626
01:02:14.919 --> 01:02:18.258
- What is it with you. anyway?
- Still think we're finished?

627
01:02:18.525 --> 01:02:20.362
More than ever.

628
01:02:25.269 --> 01:02:26.805
Sorry to wake you. sir.

629
01:02:27.039 --> 01:02:32.314
Starfleet requests any data we have on
the whereabouts of Enterprise.

630
01:02:34.317 --> 01:02:35.786
What?

631
01:02:36.053 --> 01:02:40.126
They're refusing to acknowledge
signal to return to space dock. sir.

632
01:02:43.933 --> 01:02:48.774
Signal Starfleet that we have no idea
location Enterprise.

633
01:02:49.375 --> 01:02:53.214
- Sir?
- You have hearing problems?

634
01:02:53.915 --> 01:02:55.485
No. sir.

635
01:03:37.084 --> 01:03:39.154
Klingon blood.

636
01:03:39.388 --> 01:03:44.162
They must have walked through it when
it was floating and tracked it back here.

637
01:03:44.396 --> 01:03:47.267
This is the first evidence
which corroborates our theory.

638
01:03:47.534 --> 01:03:49.604
Now we go to Starfleet?

639
01:03:49.838 --> 01:03:53.143
We expand our search
to include uniforms.

640
01:03:53.376 --> 01:03:55.480
All uniforms?

641
01:04:13.776 --> 01:04:16.414
Clear. sir. Make a hole.

642
01:04:16.647 --> 01:04:19.619
Coming through. Coming through.

643
01:04:31.237 --> 01:04:33.441
Sir! Sir!

644
01:05:02.821 --> 01:05:06.460
- I think we've been had.
- No. you weren't. Doctor.

645
01:05:06.694 --> 01:05:10.399
Get off at the first level.
Follow the gang into the mine.

646
01:05:10.666 --> 01:05:13.071
They don't take girls.

647
01:05:22.987 --> 01:05:28.128
- You are crewman Dax?
- Yes. What is the problem?

648
01:05:28.395 --> 01:05:35.072
Perhaps you know
Russian epic of Cinderella?

649
01:05:35.306 --> 01:05:38.912
If shoe fits - wear it.

650
01:05:40.281 --> 01:05:43.386
Mr Chekov...

651
01:05:56.707 --> 01:05:58.577
Watch me.

652
01:06:00.480 --> 01:06:05.287
What kind of creature is this?
Last night you two were...

653
01:06:07.725 --> 01:06:09.962
Get in.

654
01:07:17.202 --> 01:07:19.439
Come on. We don't have a lot of time.

655
01:07:36.567 --> 01:07:38.537
Hurry!

656
01:07:41.775 --> 01:07:43.978
Up there.

657
01:07:45.314 --> 01:07:47.150
Come on - climb!

658
01:07:57.767 --> 01:08:00.605
Here. you'll need these. Quickly!

659
01:08:20.937 --> 01:08:22.840
Stay close.

660
01:09:36.224 --> 01:09:38.895
- There they are.
- They emerge from the beaming shield.

661
01:09:39.563 --> 01:09:44.504
Mr Scott. start your engines.
Mr Chekov. set course for Rura Penthe.

662
01:09:44.738 --> 01:09:48.544
Mr Spock. Rura Penthe is deep inside
the Klingon frontier.

663
01:09:48.778 --> 01:09:51.048
- If we're discovered...
- Correct.

664
01:09:51.315 --> 01:09:55.489
We need a feat of linguistic legerdemain
and intrepidity -

665
01:09:55.756 --> 01:09:58.226
- before the Captain and Dr. McCoy
freeze to death.

666
01:10:05.471 --> 01:10:08.877
- Leave me. I'm finished.
- No!

667
01:10:09.110 --> 01:10:13.050
Bones. I'm wearing
a viridium patch on my back.

668
01:10:13.283 --> 01:10:17.157
Spock slapped it there
before we went on Gorkon's ship.

669
01:10:17.390 --> 01:10:19.760
That cunning little Vulcan.

670
01:10:19.994 --> 01:10:22.966
Come on! We're in the clear.

671
01:10:24.034 --> 01:10:28.441
Now that we're outside the shield.
they can locate us two sectors away.

672
01:10:28.675 --> 01:10:30.578
If they're even looking for us.

673
01:10:59.391 --> 01:11:02.663
This is listening post Morska.

674
01:11:02.896 --> 01:11:05.099
What ship is that. over?

675
01:11:15.684 --> 01:11:19.756
We must respond. A universal
translator would be recognised.

676
01:11:28.203 --> 01:11:31.575
We am thy freighter... Ursva.

677
01:11:31.809 --> 01:11:35.247
Six weeks out of...

678
01:11:35.482 --> 01:11:38.286
...Kronos.

679
01:11:51.974 --> 01:11:54.278
"What is your destination. over? "

680
01:11:58.685 --> 01:12:01.723
We is condemning food...

681
01:12:04.695 --> 01:12:07.299
...things and supplies.

682
01:12:10.838 --> 01:12:14.411
Don't catch any bugs.

683
01:12:44.325 --> 01:12:47.697
Would you mind explaining
that little trick you do?

684
01:12:47.931 --> 01:12:52.538
- I'm a Chameloid.
- I've heard about you.

685
01:12:52.772 --> 01:12:56.878
Shape-shifters.
I thought you were mythical.

686
01:12:57.446 --> 01:13:00.150
Give a girl a chance. Captain.

687
01:13:01.686 --> 01:13:03.655
It takes a lot of effort.

688
01:13:03.889 --> 01:13:06.193
I don't doubt it.

689
01:13:06.427 --> 01:13:08.897
Stop me if I'm wrong. -

690
01:13:09.132 --> 01:13:12.470
- but do we have any way of knowing
whether this is the real you?

691
01:13:12.971 --> 01:13:17.310
I thought I would assume
a pleasing shape.

692
01:13:22.352 --> 01:13:26.592
We're outside the shield.
Now it's your turn. Captain.

693
01:13:26.826 --> 01:13:29.164
If you say so.

694
01:13:29.998 --> 01:13:31.367
Are you crazy? !

695
01:13:31.600 --> 01:13:34.839
She didn't need our help. Where did you
get these convenient clothes?

696
01:13:35.073 --> 01:13:38.111
Don't tell me that flare
is standard prison issue.

697
01:13:38.344 --> 01:13:41.750
It's to let them know where we are.
Ask her what she's getting in return.

698
01:13:41.983 --> 01:13:46.357
A full pardon... which doesn't cover this.

699
01:13:46.591 --> 01:13:49.496
An accident wasn't good enough.
Come on. Spock.

700
01:13:49.730 --> 01:13:54.237
Good enough for one.
Two would have looked suspicious.

701
01:13:54.471 --> 01:13:59.645
Killed while attempting escape.
That's convincing for both.

702
01:14:03.451 --> 01:14:04.987
Surprise!

703
01:14:16.339 --> 01:14:19.377
- Your friends are late.
- They'll be along.

704
01:14:22.515 --> 01:14:25.954
- I can't believe I kissed you.
- Must have been your lifelong ambition.

705
01:14:41.512 --> 01:14:43.549
Isn't it time you became
something else?

706
01:14:43.782 --> 01:14:45.351
I like it here.

707
01:14:53.898 --> 01:14:57.370
Well. well. well...

708
01:15:04.583 --> 01:15:07.220
What took you so long?

709
01:15:07.620 --> 01:15:09.757
Kill him. he's the one.

710
01:15:10.024 --> 01:15:11.727
Not me. you idiot - him!

711
01:15:14.030 --> 01:15:17.469
- No witnesses.
- Killed while trying to escape.

712
01:15:18.171 --> 01:15:21.041
- Damned clever. if you ask me.
- It's a classic.

713
01:15:21.309 --> 01:15:24.413
- That's what he wanted.
- Who? Who wanted us killed?

714
01:15:25.215 --> 01:15:29.221
Since you're all going to die anyway.
why not tell you?

715
01:15:29.455 --> 01:15:31.359
His name is...

716
01:15:37.134 --> 01:15:43.344
Damn it! What the hell! Son of a...!
Couldn't you have waited two seconds?

717
01:15:43.578 --> 01:15:45.381
He was about to explain
the whole thing.

718
01:15:45.648 --> 01:15:48.186
- You want to go back?
- Absolutely not!

719
01:15:50.956 --> 01:15:53.327
This is the bridge.
We're still in Klingon space.

720
01:15:53.561 --> 01:15:59.470
Deck 9. remain at battle stations.
Deck 9. remain at battle stations.

721
01:16:30.820 --> 01:16:33.024
They were beamed aboard
a Federation Starship.

722
01:16:33.258 --> 01:16:36.028
I could trace...

723
01:16:40.936 --> 01:16:44.074
Escaped.

724
01:16:44.976 --> 01:16:49.751
Kirk cannot know the location of
the peace conference.

725
01:16:50.218 --> 01:16:52.354
Are you sure?

726
01:16:53.022 --> 01:16:56.662
Will you take that chance?

727
01:16:56.929 --> 01:17:00.634
Helmsman.
make course to intercept Enterprise.

728
01:17:06.778 --> 01:17:09.682
The Klingons have a Bird of Prey
that can fire while cloaked.

729
01:17:09.916 --> 01:17:12.753
- She torpedoed Gorkon's ship.
- So that's it.

730
01:17:13.020 --> 01:17:16.059
We believe that Gorkon's murderers
are aboard this ship.

731
01:17:16.292 --> 01:17:20.566
- Has the peace conference begun?
- Who knows? The location is secret.

732
01:17:20.800 --> 01:17:23.638
- There's always something.
- Captain! Mr Spock!

733
01:17:23.905 --> 01:17:27.043
I found the uniforms
with the Klingon blood on them.

734
01:17:41.667 --> 01:17:47.309
But the uniforms belong to
these two men. Burke and Samno.

735
01:17:47.943 --> 01:17:51.382
Not anymore.
Phaser on "stun" at close range.

736
01:17:51.616 --> 01:17:55.055
First rule of assassination -
kill the assassins.

737
01:17:55.556 --> 01:17:59.996
- Now we're back to square one.
- Can I talk to you?

738
01:18:01.264 --> 01:18:06.272
- Why weren't they vaporized?
- It would set off the alarm.

739
01:18:13.418 --> 01:18:15.287
It's possible.

740
01:18:15.521 --> 01:18:19.160
Now hear this. Now hear this.

741
01:18:19.393 --> 01:18:23.333
Court reporter to sick bay.
Code blue - urgent.

742
01:18:23.567 --> 01:18:27.173
Statements to be taken at once
from Yeomen Burke and Samno.

743
01:18:27.406 --> 01:18:31.546
Repeat. court reporter to sick bay.
Code blue - urgent.

744
01:18:31.780 --> 01:18:33.850
Statements to be taken.

745
01:18:34.084 --> 01:18:38.925
Repeat. statements to be taken from
Yeomen Burke and Samno.

746
01:19:15.550 --> 01:19:16.986
You have to shoot.

747
01:19:20.792 --> 01:19:25.333
If you are logical. you have to shoot.

748
01:19:29.339 --> 01:19:31.575
- I do not want to.
- What you want is irrelevant.

749
01:19:31.809 --> 01:19:35.047
What you've chosen is at hand.

750
01:19:35.282 --> 01:19:36.917
I'd just as soon you didn't.

751
01:19:44.463 --> 01:19:46.766
The operation is over.

752
01:19:52.109 --> 01:19:55.414
I did not fire.
You cannot prove anything.

753
01:19:55.648 --> 01:20:00.555
Yes. I can. At my trial my personal log
was used against me.

754
01:20:00.789 --> 01:20:04.461
How long did you wait outside
my quarters before I noticed you?

755
01:20:06.097 --> 01:20:08.301
You knew?

756
01:20:09.636 --> 01:20:12.241
I tried to tell you.
but you would not listen.

757
01:20:13.342 --> 01:20:16.280
Neither of us was hearing very well
that night.

758
01:20:16.514 --> 01:20:19.886
There were things I tried to tell you.
about having faith.

759
01:20:20.119 --> 01:20:24.727
You have betrayed the Federation.
All of you.

760
01:20:24.961 --> 01:20:28.066
- And what have you've been doing?
- Saving Starfleet.

761
01:20:28.333 --> 01:20:34.810
Klingons cannot be trusted. Sir...
You said so yourself.

762
01:20:35.043 --> 01:20:38.850
They killed your son.
Did you not wish Gorkon dead?

763
01:20:39.084 --> 01:20:43.123
"Let them die". you said.
Did I misinterpret you?

764
01:20:45.293 --> 01:20:47.129
And you were right.

765
01:20:47.364 --> 01:20:51.169
They conspired with us to assassinate
their own Chancellor.

766
01:20:51.403 --> 01:20:53.606
How trustworthy can they be?

767
01:20:53.874 --> 01:20:57.446
Klingons and Federation members
conspiring together.

768
01:20:57.713 --> 01:21:01.786
- Who is "us"?
- All who stands to lose from peace.

769
01:21:02.020 --> 01:21:03.455
Names. Lieutenant.

770
01:21:03.689 --> 01:21:08.864
My comrades will make certain
all your transmissions are jammed.

771
01:21:09.098 --> 01:21:14.106
- Names. Lieutenant!
- I do not remember.

772
01:21:16.376 --> 01:21:19.081
A lie?

773
01:21:19.315 --> 01:21:21.318
A choice.

774
01:21:25.157 --> 01:21:27.728
Spock.

775
01:22:08.893 --> 01:22:12.633
Admiral Cartwright.

776
01:22:12.867 --> 01:22:15.237
From Starfleet?

777
01:22:22.114 --> 01:22:24.552
Who else?

778
01:22:27.757 --> 01:22:31.997
General... Chang.

779
01:22:37.773 --> 01:22:44.818
- Who else?
- Romulan Ambassador and others.

780
01:22:48.724 --> 01:22:51.595
Where is the peace conference?

781
01:22:52.931 --> 01:22:55.735
Where is the peace conference?

782
01:23:27.753 --> 01:23:29.990
She does not know.

783
01:23:31.325 --> 01:23:32.861
Then we're dead.

784
01:23:43.311 --> 01:23:48.052
I have been dead before.
Contact Excelsior.

785
01:23:48.286 --> 01:23:52.125
- She'll have the co-ordinates.
- I've already got it. sir.

786
01:23:52.725 --> 01:23:55.097
- Standing by. Captain Kirk.
- Sulu.

787
01:23:55.330 --> 01:23:59.737
You realize that by even talking to us.
you're violating regulations.

788
01:23:59.971 --> 01:24:02.441
I'm sorry. Captain.
Yourmessage is breaking up.

789
01:24:02.675 --> 01:24:06.215
Bless you. Sulu.
Where is the peace conference?

790
01:24:06.448 --> 01:24:07.984
They'll attempt another assassination.

791
01:24:08.218 --> 01:24:12.992
It's at Camp Khitomer.
near the Romulan border.

792
01:24:13.226 --> 01:24:15.763
I'm sending the co-ordinates on
a coded frequency.

793
01:24:15.963 --> 01:24:18.067
We'll need more than that.

794
01:24:18.300 --> 01:24:22.006
There's a Bird of Prey on the look-out
for us that can fire when cloaked.

795
01:24:22.273 --> 01:24:24.476
Surely not.

796
01:24:24.711 --> 01:24:29.251
How many of those things are there?
Come on. Lieutenant.

797
01:24:29.519 --> 01:24:32.222
- Just the prototype.
- Do you hear that?

798
01:24:32.456 --> 01:24:35.795
I'm getting under way now.
We're in Alpha Quadrant.

799
01:24:36.028 --> 01:24:38.833
The chances of our reaching
the conference in time are slim.

800
01:24:39.066 --> 01:24:43.841
- When does this conference start?
- According to my information - today.

801
01:24:45.277 --> 01:24:48.582
- Thank you. Captain Sulu.
- Don't mention it. Captain Kirk.

802
01:24:55.092 --> 01:24:57.196
Spock?

803
01:24:57.429 --> 01:24:59.532
I prefer it dark.

804
01:25:06.143 --> 01:25:10.317
- Dining on ashes?
- You were right.

805
01:25:10.584 --> 01:25:17.294
It was arrogant presumption on my part
that got us into this situation.

806
01:25:17.528 --> 01:25:20.733
You and the Doctor
might have been killed.

807
01:25:20.967 --> 01:25:23.404
The night is young.

808
01:25:23.671 --> 01:25:28.579
You said it yourself. it was logical.
Peace is worth a few personal risks.

809
01:25:31.551 --> 01:25:33.554
You're a great one for logic.

810
01:25:33.787 --> 01:25:38.595
I'm a great one for rushing in
where angels fear to tread.

811
01:25:38.829 --> 01:25:45.072
We're both extremists. Reality is
probably somewhere in between.

812
01:25:48.711 --> 01:25:51.483
I couldn't get past the death of my son.

813
01:25:51.716 --> 01:25:56.190
I was prejudiced by her
accomplishments as a Vulcan.

814
01:25:56.423 --> 01:25:59.963
Gorkon had to die before I understood
how prejudiced I was.

815
01:26:07.975 --> 01:26:09.644
Is it possible...

816
01:26:10.446 --> 01:26:17.858
...that we two. you and I.
have grown so old and inflexible -

817
01:26:18.091 --> 01:26:22.499
- that we have outlived our usefulness?

818
01:26:22.732 --> 01:26:25.403
Would that constitute a joke?

819
01:26:26.572 --> 01:26:30.845
- It wasn't your fault.
- I was responsible.

820
01:26:31.747 --> 01:26:36.788
- For no actions but your own.
- That's not what you said at your trial.

821
01:26:37.022 --> 01:26:39.225
That was as captain of the ship.
Human beings...

822
01:26:39.459 --> 01:26:42.597
We both know that I am not human.

823
01:26:42.831 --> 01:26:46.270
Do you want to know something?
Everybody's human.

824
01:26:47.138 --> 01:26:50.844
I find that remark... insulting.

825
01:26:51.378 --> 01:26:52.647
Come. I need you.

826
01:26:57.021 --> 01:27:01.460
Madam Chancellor.
members of the diplomatic corps...

827
01:27:02.563 --> 01:27:05.334
...honoured guests.

828
01:27:05.568 --> 01:27:08.706
The United Federation of Planets
welcomes you to Camp Khitomer.

829
01:27:24.798 --> 01:27:27.269
She's out here somewhere.

830
01:27:27.502 --> 01:27:32.143
- But if she's cloaked...
- Then all we have is a radiation surge.

831
01:27:32.377 --> 01:27:36.985
By the time we're close enough
to record it. we're ashes.

832
01:27:39.555 --> 01:27:42.093
2.06...

833
01:27:44.096 --> 01:27:45.899
2.03...

834
01:27:47.001 --> 01:27:53.477
- Close enough to beam down?
- Not yet. In two minutes. 1 .58.

835
01:27:53.711 --> 01:27:56.582
Go to impulse power for Khitomer.

836
01:28:04.962 --> 01:28:09.970
Let us redefine progress to mean that
just because we can do a thing -

837
01:28:10.203 --> 01:28:14.811
- it does not necessarily follow
that we must do that thing.

838
01:28:18.083 --> 01:28:20.654
- Uhura?
- Nothing. Captain.

839
01:28:20.888 --> 01:28:23.759
If she's here.
she's rigged for silent running.

840
01:28:30.570 --> 01:28:34.009
Coming up on transporter range
in 57 seconds.

841
01:28:34.243 --> 01:28:37.648
Transporter room.
Stand by to beam down.

842
01:28:39.851 --> 01:28:42.055
53...

843
01:28:45.628 --> 01:28:48.031
48 seconds.

844
01:28:52.105 --> 01:28:54.275
44...

845
01:28:56.211 --> 01:28:59.483
I can see you. Kirk.

846
01:28:59.716 --> 01:29:01.586
Chang.

847
01:29:01.819 --> 01:29:04.157
Can you see me?

848
01:29:04.391 --> 01:29:08.865
Now be honest. Captain.
Warrior to warrior.

849
01:29:09.098 --> 01:29:12.837
You do prefer it this way. don't you?
As it was meant to be.

850
01:29:13.672 --> 01:29:16.243
No peace in our time.

851
01:29:16.443 --> 01:29:21.451
"Once more unto the breach.
dearfriends. "

852
01:29:36.408 --> 01:29:39.380
- This is fun.
- Reverse engines. All astern.

853
01:29:39.614 --> 01:29:41.650
One and a half impulse power. Back off!

854
01:29:45.790 --> 01:29:48.427
What's she doing?

855
01:29:49.096 --> 01:29:51.666
What's she waiting for?

856
01:29:51.866 --> 01:29:55.505
Probably attempting to ascertain
why we are reversing.

857
01:29:55.740 --> 01:29:58.744
Wondering whether we detect her.

858
01:30:02.817 --> 01:30:04.453
Incoming!

859
01:30:08.426 --> 01:30:10.697
- In range?
- Not yet. sir.

860
01:30:10.964 --> 01:30:12.400
Come on!

861
01:30:12.633 --> 01:30:14.303
- She'll fly apart.
- Fly her apart. then!

862
01:30:14.569 --> 01:30:19.911
Many speculated about
my father's motives.

863
01:30:20.145 --> 01:30:25.086
Some said he was an idealist.
Others said he had no choice.

864
01:30:25.320 --> 01:30:30.628
If Praxis had not exploded. his idealism
wouldn't have found expression.

865
01:30:32.030 --> 01:30:34.134
We are a proud race.

866
01:30:34.368 --> 01:30:38.808
We are here because we intend
to go on being proud.

867
01:30:48.223 --> 01:30:51.862
- Go to auxiliary power!
- Auxiliary circuits destroyed.

868
01:30:57.772 --> 01:31:01.911
"Tickle us. do we not laugh?
Prick us. do we not bleed?"

869
01:31:02.580 --> 01:31:06.953
"Wrong us. shall we not revenge?"

870
01:31:07.186 --> 01:31:08.555
Gas.

871
01:31:10.258 --> 01:31:14.832
Gas. Captain. Under impulse power
she expands fuel. like all vessels.

872
01:31:15.066 --> 01:31:20.274
We call it "plasma".
but it is merely ionised gas.

873
01:31:20.508 --> 01:31:25.149
What about our equipment
to catalogue gaseous anomalies?

874
01:31:27.185 --> 01:31:29.289
The thing's got to have a tail-pipe.

875
01:31:29.523 --> 01:31:33.629
Doctor. would you assist me
in performing surgery on a torpedo?

876
01:31:33.896 --> 01:31:36.033
Fascinating.

877
01:31:37.134 --> 01:31:39.071
Hard to starboard.

878
01:31:40.573 --> 01:31:44.780
The proposed agenda is as follows:
The evacuation of Kronos -

879
01:31:45.014 --> 01:31:48.252
- has been calculated
within the 50 Earth year time span.

880
01:31:48.486 --> 01:31:50.924
Phase 1 - preparation for evacuation...

881
01:32:00.772 --> 01:32:05.780
Captain. she's packing quite a wallop.
Shields weakening.

882
01:32:12.090 --> 01:32:16.931
Shields up! Alright. now we're giving
them something else to shoot at.

883
01:32:23.742 --> 01:32:26.881
The game's afoot.

884
01:32:33.525 --> 01:32:37.732
- Excelsior's been hit!
- "Our revels now are ended". Kirk.

885
01:32:45.811 --> 01:32:51.120
"Cry havoc.
and let slip the dogs of war."

886
01:32:51.687 --> 01:32:55.059
- Bones. where's my torpedo?
- Bet you wished you'd stayed in bed.

887
01:32:57.396 --> 01:33:00.101
Shields collapsing!

888
01:33:01.203 --> 01:33:03.239
The key. please. Time is short.

889
01:33:11.486 --> 01:33:14.056
- The hull has been compromised.
- I wonder how bad.

890
01:33:14.256 --> 01:33:15.692
Connect echo-bars.

891
01:33:15.925 --> 01:33:18.196
...discuss the report on phase 2.

892
01:33:18.430 --> 01:33:21.702
- Alter circuit A.
- Sensor.

893
01:33:21.935 --> 01:33:24.372
...we commence
within minutes of the preparation.

894
01:33:24.640 --> 01:33:29.113
- "I am constant as the Northern star."
- I'd give real money. if he'd shut up.

895
01:33:29.782 --> 01:33:31.016
Plate. please.

896
01:33:31.284 --> 01:33:32.786
...and assimilation will consume...

897
01:33:33.020 --> 01:33:34.923
We've got a heart beat.

898
01:33:36.124 --> 01:33:37.860
...with the Klingon Empire...

899
01:33:38.128 --> 01:33:39.731
Key. please.

900
01:33:39.964 --> 01:33:41.834
- Where's that torpedo?
- She's ready.

901
01:33:42.067 --> 01:33:44.471
Lock and load!

902
01:33:45.873 --> 01:33:47.576
Fire!

903
01:33:59.361 --> 01:34:02.500
"To be... or not"...

904
01:34:03.135 --> 01:34:04.771
..."to be."

905
01:34:06.106 --> 01:34:08.008
Target that explosion and fire.

906
01:34:10.413 --> 01:34:12.249
Fire!

907
01:34:21.598 --> 01:34:25.270
This work will occupy us
throughout most of the week.

908
01:34:25.504 --> 01:34:26.873
I hope that the delegation -

909
01:34:27.106 --> 01:34:33.917
- can implement the provisions
of Phase 1 by the first of next month.

910
01:34:34.151 --> 01:34:37.723
As you know. time is of the essence.

911
01:34:37.956 --> 01:34:39.425
Out of the way!

912
01:34:44.467 --> 01:34:46.170
Mr President!

913
01:34:47.472 --> 01:34:49.408
Mr President!

914
01:34:50.844 --> 01:34:52.647
Kirk. Enterprise.

915
01:34:54.483 --> 01:34:56.052
Protect the Chancellor!

916
01:35:03.163 --> 01:35:06.168
- Arrest those men!
- Arrest yourself!

917
01:35:10.843 --> 01:35:12.979
We've got a full confession.

918
01:35:27.436 --> 01:35:31.509
- This is not Klingon blood.
- Cartwright. Just a minute.
